<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Traulsen service</p>
    <h2>The "buy once, cry once" of American commercial refrigeration.</h2>

    <p>Traulsen is the "buy once, cry once" of American commercial refrigeration. Premium tier, manufactured in Fort Worth, Texas since 1938. Now part of ITW Food Equipment Group (Illinois Tool Works), sister brands include Hobart, Vulcan, Stero, and Baxter. Popular in chain restaurants where reliability matters more than upfront cost: Marriott hotel kitchens, Hilton properties, hospital food service operations, university dining halls, military food service.</p>

    <p>We service Traulsen across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>G-Series</strong> mid-tier reach-ins (G10010 single, G20010 double, G30010 triple, cooler and -011 freezer variants). <strong>R-Series and RH-Series</strong> premium reach-ins. <strong>RIH-Series</strong> hospital-grade heavy duty. <strong>A-Series</strong> including ARI/ARIF pass-through and AHT heavy duty. <strong>RBC</strong> back-bar bottle coolers. <strong>TR</strong> worktables and chef bases. <strong>RDT</strong> refrigerated drawers. <strong>RUC</strong> undercounter refrigerators.</p>

    <p>EPA 608 Universal plus R-290 certification (post-2018 Traulsen R-290 transition). CSLB #1138898. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608 verifiable.</a></p>

    <p>Industry-leading reliability means Traulsen service intervals are longer than competitors, but when service is needed, parts logistics through ITW Food Equipment network is 5 to 7 day standard ship from Texas. We work directly with the ITW parts system.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Series-aware diagnosis</p>
    <h2>The Traulsen lineup, and what fails on each tier.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Traulsen uses a clear tier hierarchy across reach-in, prep, undercounter, worktable, and back-bar formats. G-Series is mid-tier within Traulsen (still premium by industry standard). R-Series and RH-Series are top tier. RIH is hospital-grade heavy duty. A-Series covers pass-through and heavy duty kitchen specs.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">G-Series Reach-Ins (G-Series Spec Line)</h3>
    <p>The mid-tier within Traulsen, still premium by industry standard. G10010 (single-door cooler), G20010 (double), G30010 (triple). Freezer variants are -011 (G10011, G20011, G30011). Common in chain restaurants and hospitality.</p>
    <p>Common failures (Traulsen-specific patterns):</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 7 to 10:</strong> Condenser fan motor (longer life than mid-tier brands due to higher-quality OEM components)</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8 to 12:</strong> Defrost heater on freezer variants (electric defrost similar to True T-49F architecture)</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6 to 8:</strong> Door gasket compression. Traulsen gaskets last longer than industry standard (5-year warranty vs 1 to 2 year competitors)</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10+:</strong> Compressor capacitor / start relay</li>
      <li><strong>Year 12 to 15+:</strong> Compressor mechanical wear</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">R-Series Premium / RH-Series</h3>
    <p>Top tier within Traulsen. Premium components, longer warranties. RH series stands for "Reach-In Heavy" or premium spec. Common in upscale hotels and premium restaurants.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">RIH Hospital Tier</h3>
    <p>Heavy-duty stainless construction, premium components, designed for healthcare food service. We service these in LA-area hospitals and senior care facilities. Designed for 18 to 25+ year institutional service life.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">A-Series Pass-Through (ARI, ARIF) and AHT</h3>
    <p>Back-to-back access reach-ins for prep line setups. Common in high-volume restaurants and institutional food service. AHT covers heavy duty kitchen tier.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">RBC / TBC Back-Bar and TR Worktables</h3>
    <p>Bar-side refrigeration with premium build for hotel bars and upscale establishments. TR refrigerated worktables and chef bases for prep stations.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">RDT Drawers / RUC Undercounter / G-Series Prep Tables</h3>
    <p>RDT drawer-style refrigeration for prep stations. RUC undercounter refrigerators with premium build vs True TUC or Turbo Air TUC at higher price point. G-Series prep tables apply the same G-Series quality to sandwich/salad prep variants.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TYPICAL FAILURES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top Traulsen repairs we see in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on Traulsen service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Door gasket replacement.</strong> Even with 5-year warranty, eventually wears in heavy-use environments.</li>
      <li><strong>Condenser fan motor.</strong> Longer service life than competitors but eventually fails. Traulsen OEM via ITW parts network.</li>
      <li><strong>Defrost heater (G-011, R-Series freezer variants).</strong> Electric defrost element, replacement requires evap access.</li>
      <li><strong>Compressor capacitor plus start relay.</strong> Replace as a pair on aged compressors.</li>
      <li><strong>Smart-Eye control diagnostic (newer models).</strong> Traulsen Smart-Eye electronic controls have diagnostic codes. We read them and identify failures faster than legacy diagnostic.</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigerant leak repair (any age).</strong> EPA 608 leak detection plus brazed repair plus recharge. Post-2018 R-290 systems require R-290 certification.</li>
      <li><strong>Hospital-grade gasket service (RIH).</strong> Heavier-duty gaskets for healthcare food service.</li>
      <li><strong>Pass-through configuration service (A-Series ARI/ARIF).</strong> Both-side access requires understanding of dual-door synchronization.</li>
      <li><strong>Back-bar service (RBC, TBC).</strong> Bar splash damage cleanup, drink residue in components.</li>
      <li><strong>ITW warranty processing.</strong> Traulsen warranties processed through ITW Food Equipment Group network.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five Traulsen jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marriott hotel kitchen in Beverly Hills · Traulsen G20010 double-door cooler (11 years, R-134a)</h3>
        <p>Temp climbing in left section. Diagnosed: condenser fan motor end-of-life (11-year service is exceptional; most mid-tier brands fail at 7 to 9 years). Replaced motor (Traulsen OEM via ITW parts, 5-day standard ship). Total: $120 plus $410 part plus 1.5 hours = $580. Hotel impressed with longevity and replacement service.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hospital cafeteria in Pasadena · Traulsen RIH132LP-FHS hospital reach-in cooler (14 years)</h3>
        <p>Refrigerant slow leak. EPA 608 leak detection: leak at evap brazed joint. Pumped down, brazed repair, evacuated to 500 microns, recharged R-134a to nameplate. Hospital food service procurement appreciated quick turnaround. Total: $120 plus $480 refrigerant plus $720 labor = $1,320. 14-year service interval for first major repair: industry-leading.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>University dining hall in Westwood · Traulsen ARI232LP-FHS pass-through reach-in (9 years)</h3>
        <p>Both-side door alignment off, doors not closing fully on prep-side. Diagnosed: hinge alignment drift (heavy use 200+ cycles per side per day). Realigned hinges on both sides, replaced hinge bushings. Total: $120 plus $290 parts plus 2 hours = $580.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hilton hotel back-bar in Santa Monica · Traulsen RBC76 back-bar bottle cooler (8 years)</h3>
        <p>Warming during Saturday night service. Diagnosed: refrigerant low plus door gasket compressed (combination failure typical at 8 years). Recharged refrigerant plus replaced both door gaskets. Total: $120 plus $480 parts plus 2 hours = $720.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Senior care facility in Calabasas · Traulsen G30011 triple-door freezer (13 years)</h3>
        <p>Defrost heater open-circuit on left zone. Diagnosed: defrost heater element burnout. Replaced element via ITW parts (5-day ship, Texas distribution). Facility procurement managed warranty processing through ITW. Total: $120 plus $580 part plus 2.5 hours = $890. 13-year service interval for first defrost heater replacement.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

